sudo rm -f /etc/docker/daemon.json
Step 2 — Create new file:
sudo tee /etc/docker/daemon.json > /dev/null <<'EOF'
{
  "insecure-registries": ["100.48.195.166", "172.31.2.177", "localhost"]
}
EOF
Step 3 — Verify it saved:
sudo cat /etc/docker/daemon.json
It must show the IPs! ✅
Step 4 — Restart Docker:
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl restart docker
Step 5 — Confirm IPs are loaded:
sudo docker info | grep -A5 -i insecure
Now it must show 100.48.195.166 in the list!
Step 6 — Login:
cd ~/harbor && sudo docker compose up -d
sudo docker login 100.48.195.166
